name: Standing Barbell Calf Raise
description: 1. Place something such as 25lb weights on the ground to increase your range of motion 2. Using a barbell position yourself under the barbell so that it may rest on your upper back and brace the bar with an overhand grip 3. Step onto the slightly elevated platform you set down with your toes with your heels remaining on the ground 4. Rise up on your toes as high as you can 5. Slowly return down with heels to the ground and repeat for desired reps
variations: Smith Machine Standing Calf Raise, Dumbbell Standing Calf Raise
